Key Findings
Overall Churn Rate: 26.54%
Month-to-Month contracts showed the highest churn rate (42.71%).
Fiber Optic customers had significantly higher churn rates than DSL customers.
Electronic Check users demonstrated the highest churn among payment methods.
Customers without Online Security and Tech Support were more likely to churn.
Most customer churn occurred within the first 12 months.
Long-tenure customers generated the highest customer lifetime value.

Recommendations
Promote annual and multi-year subscription plans.
Improve customer onboarding during the first year.
Bundle value-added services such as Online Security and Tech Support.
Encourage automated payment methods.
Develop retention campaigns targeting high-risk customers.

